# Credentials for live-shows tools/youtube scripts
# ------------------------------------
# Copy this file to .env (in the same directory where the scripts live) and fill in your values.
# .env is gitignored and must never be committed.

# YouTube Data API key (read-only, used by youtube_fetch.py)
# Get from: Google Cloud Console → APIs & Services → Credentials → API Keys
YOUTUBE_API_KEY=your_api_key_here

# OAuth client secrets file (used by youtube_create_playlists.py)
# Download from: Google Cloud Console → Credentials → OAuth 2.0 Client IDs
YOUTUBE_CLIENT_SECRETS=client_secrets.json

# OAuth token cache file (auto-generated on first auth run — do not edit manually)
YOUTUBE_TOKEN_FILE=token.json

# Spotify API credentials (used by youtube_fill_handles.py)
# Create a free app at: https://developer.spotify.com/dashboard
# Set any Redirect URI (e.g. http://localhost) — it is not used by this script.
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID=your_spotify_client_id_here
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_SECRET=your_spotify_client_secret_here

HOWTO ONLY - DO NOT STORE THESE TOKENS HERE - STORE THEM IN YOUR PASSWORD MANAGER

# GitHub Personal Access Tokens (used by index.html auth modal for Decision and notes edits)
# Create tokens at: https://github.com/settings/personal-access-tokens/new
# Type: Fine-grained · Repository: your repo (and your private sidecar if enabled)
# Permissions: Contents → Read and write · Issues → Read and write
# Paste it into the index.html auth modal (🔑 auth button) when editing Decisions.

# If you implement recommendations, you will want an even more fine-grained token
# only for Issues Read + Write in your public repo. This token needs to be stored in app.js
# and is deliberately concatenated there to get around token-blocking when you check it in

# For some of the agentic playbooks, you will want a third token
# in addition to the above permissions, add Pull requests → Read and write, Workflows Read and write

